{
  "text": "Note that we evaluate \u03ba for different antenna configurations in Sec. IV. Since the maximum cross product of any two steering vectors is M , we see that 0 \u2264 \u03ba \u2264 1. Furthermore, if the independent rays in (21) correspond to two different users then \u03ba is seen to be a measure of the normalized interference between the rays. This interpretation is further explored in Sec. VII. Note that \u03ba was also found to be an important performance metric in [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "5033249"
